In thin layer chromatography using hexane, the least polar compound will rise to maximum height and most polar compound will rise to minimum height.<br/><br/>
$\therefore \mathrm{R}_{\mathrm{f}}$ value for most polar compound<br/><br/>
$$
\begin{aligned}
& =\frac{2}{8}=0.25 \\\\
& =25 \times 10^{-2}
\end{aligned}
$$
